<ul><li>For&nbsp;<b>light isotopes</b>&nbsp;(Z &lt; 20), the stable nuclei follows the straight line&nbsp;\(N=Z\), and have&nbsp;<b>equal numbers of protons and neutrons</b>.</li><li>For Z &gt; 20, stable nuclei have&nbsp;<b>more neutrons than protons</b>, so the neutron/proton ratio increases.</li><li>\(\alpha\)<b>&nbsp;emitters</b>&nbsp;occur beyond&nbsp;\(Z=60\).</li></ul>